cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with information theory and communication efficiency in networks, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The focus on function computation in collocated networks suggests that it could also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of single-letter information measures and the exploration of scaling laws suggest that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
